Fusion Telecommunications International, Inc. (FSNN) Receives An Update From Brokers


 By Ashley Brown /  in  Stocks /  on  Friday, 21 Jul 2017 07:25 AM  / 0 Comments




Analysts reviewing Fusion Telecommunications International, Inc. have recently updated their recommended buy/sell ratings and price targets on the stock.  			         



Based on their most recently released notes to investors, 0 analysts have a rating of “buy”, 2 analysts “outperform”, 0 analysts “hold”, 0 analysts “underperform” and 0 analysts “sell”.
Ratings and price target breakdown:
 04/26/2017 – B. Riley began new coverage on Fusion Telecommunications International, Inc. giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 3 price target on the stock.
 01/04/2017 – Craig-Hallum began new coverage on Fusion Telecommunications International, Inc. giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 3 price target on the stock.
 07/09/2015 – H.C. Wainwright began new coverage on Fusion Telecommunications International, Inc. giving the company a “” rating.
 05/20/2015 – Fusion Telecommunications International, Inc. was upgraded to “” by analysts at Zacks.
Fusion Telecommunications International, Inc. has a 50 day moving average of 1.41 and a 200 day moving average of 1.49. The stock’s market capitalization is 32.50M, it has a 52-week low of 0.96 and a 52-week high of 2.46. 
The share price of the company (FSNN) was up +2.84%, with a high of 1.48 during the day and the volume of Fusion Telecommunications International, Inc. shares traded was 47273.  



Fusion Telecommunications International, Inc. is a United States-based provider of integrated cloud solutions, including cloud voice, cloud connectivity, cloud infrastructure, cloud computing, and managed cloud-based applications to businesses, and voice over Internet Protocol (VoIP)-based voice services to carriers. The Company operates through two segments: Business Services and Carrier Services. Through Business Services segment, it provides cloud voice, cloud connectivity, cloud infrastructure, cloud computing and managed cloud-based applications to businesses of all sizes. Its suite of business services includes unified communications as a service, session initiation protocol trunking solution and file sharing solution. The Carrier Services segment includes termination of domestic and international carrier traffic utilizing VoIP technology. It offers solutions to small, medium and large businesses. It offers domestic and international VoIP services to carriers around the world.


