Global Telecom Cloud Market to Reach $38.54 Billion by 2022 


































































 




























Global Telecom Cloud Market to Reach $38.54 Billion by 2022

Geeks News Desk



BroadwayWorld.com


Jul. 18, 2017
 
 

Tweet



Share


 




 ROCKVILLE, Md., July 18, 2017 /PRNewswire/ The global telecom cloud market is set to reach $38.54 billion by 2022, according to Global Telecom Cloud MarketBy Type, By End User, By Application, By Region, Competition Forecast & Opportunities, 2012 2022, a report recently released by TechSci Research. Major players operating in the global telecom cloud market include AT&T Inc., Verizon Communication Inc., BT Group plc, CenturyLink Inc., China Telecommunication Corporation, Telus Corporation, Deutsche Telekom AG, Fusion Telecommunications International Inc., Telstra Corporation Limited ADR, NTT Communications, TATA Communications, Singapore Telecommunications Limited, ZTE Corporation, International Business Machines (IBM) and Telefonaktiebolaget LM Ericsson.
The telecom cloud market across the globe has been growing rapidly on back of increasing need to minimize operational and administrative costs of telecom companies. Increasing deployment in BFSI sector and in media and entertainment industry is channelling demand for telecom cloud across the globe. Unified Communication and Collaboration is gaining immense popularity among telecom service providers because of the better and more efficient service quality. Demand for Communication Defined Network services is also growing across the globe due to increasing need for responding quickly to user queries.
These and other key insights are featured in Global Telecom Cloud Market By Type, By End User, By Application, By Region, Competition Forecast & Opportunities, 2012 2022. 
The report provides market information of the following product type: 

Service

Unified Communication and Collaboration
Content Delivery Network
Others
Solution

Network Services
Colocation Services
Professional Services
Managed Services
More information about the report is available at https://www.marketresearch.com/TechSci-Research-v3895/Global-Telecom-Cloud-Type-Services-10880657/ 
About TechSci ResearchTechSci Research is a global market research and consulting company which provides research solutions to its customers worldwide, spanning a range of verticals. The company provides syndicated research reports, custom research solutions, data analytics and online paneling services for a variety of industry verticals including IT & Telecom, Pharmaceuticals & Healthcare, Automotive, BFSI, Retail and Consumer Goods. These solutions and services include Customer Satisfaction Studies, Competitive and Business Intelligence, Channel Partner Research, Market Opportunity Assessment, Brand Health Trackers, Disease and Treatment Patterns, Brand Assessment and Buyer Behavior studies and many more. 
Featured titles include:
